<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>He will try his best to make you feel that because Palestinians &quot;don't exist&quot; in his view, that killing Palestinians is less evil than killing other people.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Killing Palestinians is not &quot;less evil&quot; than killing other people, however when Palestinians are actively murdering your citizens, there is a right to self defense, regardless of who you hold responsible for starting the conflict.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>That Jews are absolutely right 100% of the time and that every Palestinian is equally guilty and supports terrorism.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Jews are not infallible, but Israel is a democracy, the only free nation in the entire region (except for Turkey).  Not every Palestinian is guilty and supports terrorism either, but most of them do, and most of the ones who don't will not tell you so.  Why?  They are not free to do so.  They are not free to truly oppose Arafat or the terrorism which runs rampant through their society and culture.  You will see the occasional dissident; I read an article by the father of a suicide bomber who was sickened by his son's life being thrown away.  Far too many other fathers are beamingly proud.  It is wrong to say that they all support it.  It is not incorrect to say that it is a widespread, culturally accepted and even mandated policy, which is a great deal of the problem.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>He will completely ignore the fact that there is terrible wrong on both sides, but more importantly he will ignore the fact that most people are just trying to live their lives and are not even involved, but are still being killed by both sides.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am very well aware that nearly every single Israeli would like nothing more than to live their life in peace.  I am also aware of many sad stories, especially by Palestinians, about Israeli soldiers killing their children when they broke curfew to buy chocolate or other such actions.  These are horrible, regrettable incidents, but they are the necessary byproducts of a war which is perpetuated NOT by Israel, but by Palestinians.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The historical coincidence that his own side of politics was responsible for the massacre of Jews during WW2 may even be twisted to give today's right-wing Israeli government license to kill at will.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
&quot;Side of politics&quot;?  Get a grip... you are more intelligent than that.  I can't believe you do not understand the difference between a modern &quot;conservative&quot; and a fascist like Hitler.  I do not recognize nor claim Hitler for my &quot;side&quot; of politics any more than you do so with Stalin, Mao, or the various eco-terrorists who have been popping up here and there.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you call him on it, he will inform you that Communists killed people just like the Nazis, serving as a convenient distraction from the fact that any such killing is wrong.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Much as this whole argument serves as a distraction from the fact that the Israelis are not herding Palestinians into camps where they are systematically starved and/or incinerated or gassed to death, but rather enforcing curfews, raiding homes of known terrorists and terrorist leaders, etc. etc.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Right-wing politics is all done to a formula of hate, not heartfelt belief. Dumai is just a disciple of right-wing web sites that exist to support the belief in getting richer by destroying the environment and abandoning minority groups such as the Palestinians.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
This is where you go so wrong, so often, Grozzer.  I can't understand how someone as intelligent as you can honestly believe that an entire collection of people who profess a certain value system and set of beliefs are filled only with raging emotional hatred, and have no true, thought out beliefs.  This one quote alone should trigger a warning flag in everyone's mind... and it makes me unhappily realize that arguing with Grozzer is indeed futile, as he ascribes to all &quot;right-wingers&quot; the sort of unreasoning unwillingness to even consider others' beliefs that he himself posesses.<br>
 <p>Caledhon TelRana - Champion<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51701"><br>
