<br>
I consider myself extremely moderate and can often appreciate some of the things both Grozzer and Dumai say - often on an issue-by-issue basis (I certainly am against US war in the mideast, but I also am horribly against socialism and couldn't care less about the environment).  But watching Grozzer and Dumai argue has the unfortunate effect oftentimes of seeing both of them slip too deeply into the extremes of their ideals and attacking one another on that merit, completely losing sight of the actual issue being discussed at hand.<br>
<br>
I use Grozzer and Dumai's names *only* as good examples of extremists arguing, and the effect it has - this is in NO way meant to single either of them out. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erlaak>Erlaak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://perso.club-internet.fr/darkhelm/misc/doom.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/17/03 12:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=327.topic&index=119>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://perso.club-internet.fr/darkhelm/sig.gif height=150 width=75></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: War on Iraq.  Where do you fall?</span><hr size=1> I could quote Cal's post, but i'd have to repeat what i already said.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Erlaak, I'd side more on the Palestinian side if 1967 never occurred, or if Israel had started the 1967 war. Your claims of Israel wanting all the land is laughable, since they wouldn't be in the west bank if it wasn't for their neighbor's aggressions. Jordan and Egypt picked a fight and got their asses handed to them.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
