<br>
And tell me something : if the Israelis (again, i don't like to say &quot;the Israelis&quot;, and i don't like to say &quot;the Palestinians&quot;, it generalizes too much) don't want the whole territory, then why the hell did the Israelis started to build new colonies in Palestine after they had agreed (Rabin government actualy) to stop? I mean... at last they were *almost* in peace, some Israelis and Palestinians even lived together... and were friends!<br>
They very well knew that the dust had just started to settle down...<br>
and that such a move would set the powders on fire again... that and all what i said above (the &quot;stuff&quot; that resulted into the 2nd Inti Fada).<br>
<br>
If someone knows, if i missed a part of History, please tell us.<br>
<br>
I'd like to know a few things : at that time, could they afford to occupy all the conquered countries, knowing that there would be a strong resistance?<br>
<br>
<br>
