 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caledhontelrana>Caledhon TelRana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 421<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/17/03 7:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=327.topic&index=132>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> My reaction is the same... oh, please.  Sharon wants peace, the difference is that he believes that dealing harshly with the Palestinians is a better response to their terrorism than patting them on the head and saying &quot;Be nice, now...&quot;<br>
<br>
Like I posted above... whether you believe this policy is a good one or not, the fact remains that Israeli policy has always been one of reluctant war.  The hardliners believe that military retaliation to acts of terrorism against them will help reduce such acts; that by rooting out those who plan and commit acts of terrorism they can prevent it, and hopefully show the Palestinians that terror will only win them hardship.  Whether this is a good idea or not, I'm not sure.  But merely because they take this stance does not mean that they do not want peace, as an overall goal, merely that they are willing to use military force to enforce a cease-fire until the Palestinians come back to the table.  The end goal remains the same.  I just don't understand why you honestly think that Sharon wants perpetual war.  Even if you believe he is some sort of bloodthirsty monster, the only way he could have gotten into the position of power that he now holds would have been to deceive honest Israelis into voting for him, based on the belief that he does, in the end, want peace.  How stupid would you have to be, a tiny nation submerged in a sea of hostile enemies, constantly subjected to horrible attacks, to not want peace with them?  Of course Israel wants peace.<br>
<br>
Merton... if you're going to make claims that wild, you'd better back them up with something, because I call complete bullshit on that story, or at least its undertones of &quot;Israel bombed them to keep the war going.&quot;  If it did happen, I'd be willing to bet that all anyone knew was that a bunch of terrorists were gathering together in one place... sounds like a great target for a bunch of bombs to me.  Now go back to my links... browse through MEMRI... take a look over there at statements released by Hamas and other Palestinians, then come back to me with a straight face and say that the Palestinians want peace more than the Israelis. <p>Caledhon TelRana - Champion<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=51701"><br>
